The paper presents a method for reducing and partitioning large datasets for supervised training, which is a common problem in machine learning. The paper focuses on classification tasks and uses clustering algorithms and approximate nearest neighbor methods to construct an information graph of the underlying classification patterns. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), and Data Mining (cs.DM).
